{
  "stem": "19807.3",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 65.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And the saddest thing that happened during that time, a lot of the-- those males have come-- have come from Greece, actually from Thrace and Macedonia.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And now those males were conscripted there.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And they were working with the rest of the Jews from Bulgaria.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Now, those were territories which were annexed-- were given to the king as a present from the Nazis, because he did not fight the Nazis, because he became their ally.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "I'm not going to get into any controversy, but what it is that he did not have jurisdiction over those areas.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "The fact that he had jurisdiction over us, I'm here.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "Unfortunately, it's a very bad stain on the Bulgarian people, and they admit it themselves, that the Jews from Thrace and from Macedonia were shipped out to the camps.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And as they were going with the trains through the camps, many areas the same men who were part of their families, they saw their families depart to the camps.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "Those, after they were sent back home-- after they completed their work over the winters, they would be sent home.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "All of a sudden I see different young, handsome men, young men, strong men, they would be speaking Greek.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And eventually, they began to speak Bulgarian.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And they would speak Greek and Ladino.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So they were taken by our community and they were put in different homes, and whoever had more room-- right across the street from me there were two of those fellows that were housed in that area, because they had larger quarters than we did.",
      "word_count": 45
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we were slated to take one too, like I said.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But-- but those were people, like I said, from the Greek origin in Macedonia and Thrace, that they were spared because they were conscripted as-- Laborers",
      "word_count": 26
    }
  ],
